\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 
With Martin Harris got on well, became close friend, walking holidays. Excellent vice-chancellor, outgoing, comfortable with wide range of people, refreshing change. More pragmatic, man of the world, plugged into government, more flexible view of what a u
n
iversity should be. Only VC for five years, step to a larger university. Main legacy Psychology Department, also Day Nursery. Brought teaching of nursing to university but regional body changed policy, lost to Anglia Polytechnic University. Was right to b
ring in health professional training. Brought more open accessible style to managing university.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs24\lang1033\langfe2057\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp2057 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Ron Johnston came when Ivor became PVC. Political geographer, serious academic, prolific writer, had been running Sheffield as PVC. Enjoyed Sheffield as big c
ity university in Labour city, liked its people. Never happy at Essex, did not enjoy local Tory landowners. Hard to let go of academic work. Difficult time for university, shortfall of student recruitment, Eddie Newcomb replaced by Fraser Woodburn as Regi
strar at same time. Nursing scheme failed. Little scope for positive moves. Resigned suddenly after two and a half years. Ivor became acting VC for seven months.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Enjoyed being PVC Academic. Felt attached to university. New set of challenges and problems, but knew the people. Found some management issues intellectually challenging.

\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 As VC did not start with blueprint. Clear that university\rquote 
s strength in small number of very able scholars and researchers, had to be looked after, Essex could only compete on basis of quality of its academics. Knew that university\rquote s finances not sustainable, and that some departments \endash 
 Physics, Chemistry \endash  could not continue losing so much money. Knew had to establish better local and regional relations, though very time-consum
ing, needs patience. Knew needed to re-balance with more professional departments. Opportunity to expand with outposts came only later; insufficient demand for places in Colchester. Did not originally have concept of Essex becoming a regional university. 
Did not believe there was a real opportunity to make money with research for business.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Most important achievements: to remain a high quality research university, as current RAE again shows; doubling of student numbers reduces university\rquote 
s vulnerability to takeover or merger; regional standing now far higher, through both social and professional relationships \endash  went beyond county set to local professions, politicians, NHS, business, schools.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Not clear yet whether outposts programme will succeed. Hopeful about Southend, Ipswich problematic. Now thinks Research Park was a mistake, very expensive, little outcome.

\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Was fortunate as VC, Essex civilised university, got a lot of support. Enjoyed it, but felt that 12 years was enough.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 Later personal and family 
life: married Jill 1968. Three children born 1972, 1974, 1977, brought up in Victorian house in Colchester, went to local primary schools; Deborah to Girls High School, boys to Ipswich School. Deborah did PPE, became civil servant in Home Office, now on s
e
condment reorganising London health service, married, three children. Elder son criminologist at Cambridge, did Pd D at Essex with Sean Nixon, on prisons. Younger son Daniel also PPE at University College Oxford, now commissioning editor for Profile Books
. Able to see them often.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 
Jill did degree in French at UCL, taught, then re-trained as psychotherapist; worked for local surgery with contracts in Rowhedge and university. Shared interesting anonymous insights on student life.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 
Leisure, most enjoys talking, eating and drinking with friends. Friends either from student years or later university contacts or a few local. Also enjoys theatre, opera, music, galleries. Walking holidays with friends. Skiing with family.
\par \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7684861 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b0\f42\fs22\insrsid7929874\charrsid7684861 No really wors
t thing. Fortunate life, largely to plan. Slight regret, would have liked more political public life. Best thing, apart from personal and domestic, enormously enjoyed being President of Universities UK for two years. Enjoyed writing.
